feed.title: Willow Lane Announces Major Agreements with Boost Run
feed.summary: Willow Lane Acquisition Corporation Class A (WLAC) announced major commercial agreements with Boost Run on December 15, 2025. These agreements, including a $127 million contract with Fluidstack and partnerships with Dell, aim to expand Boost Run’s access to next-generation hardware, data center capacity, capital, and new customer commitments. This initiative is designed to enhance Boost Run’s AI infrastructure capabilities and support its growth, positioning it to manage AI industry supply constraints.

feed.title: Willow Lane Acquisition Corp and Boost Run Announce Strategic Partnerships
feed.summary: Willow Lane Acquisition Corp and Boost Run have announced new commercial agreements focused on enhancing AI infrastructure. Boost Run secured a $127M contract with Fluidstack for AI compute, placed new GPU supply orders, and expanded data center partnerships. The company aims to deploy $250M in GPU capacity by Q1 2026, supported by financing agreements with Dell and Data Sales.

feed.title: Boost Run Expands AI Infrastructure Ecosystem with Additional GPU, Data Center, Financing, and Customer Partnerships as it Prepares to Merge with Willow Lane Acquisition Corp.

These agreements, including a $127 million contract with Fluidstack and partnerships with Dell Technologies, are crucial as Boost Run prepares to merge with Willow Lane Acquisition Corp. The expansion is expected to significantly increase GPU deployment to at least $250 million in Q1 2026, while maintaining a focus on profitable growth and unit economics.

feed.title: WLAC details Boost Run combination; S-4 proxy/prospectus to follow - Stock Titan
feed.summary: Willow Lane Acquisition Corp. (WLAC) issued a Form 425 communication detailing its proposed business combination with Boost Run through a new Delaware "Pubco." The transaction, structured as a two-step merger, will require the filing of an S-4 registration statement including a proxy statement/prospectus, followed by a shareholder vote by Willow Lane shareholders. The communication also outlines various risks associated with the transaction, such as completion timing, Nasdaq listing requirements for Pubco's securities, and potential redemption levels.

feed.title: WLAC to merge with Boost Run at $614M post‑money valuation - Stock Titan
feed.summary: Willow Lane Acquisition Corp. (WLAC) announced a proposed business combination with Boost Run Holdings, LLC, which is expected to result in a combined company named Boost Run Inc. The deal values the combined entity at $614 million post-money, assuming 100% of the funds remain in Willow Lane's trust account. The companies plan to file a Form S-4 with the SEC, and the communication highlights various risk factors associated with the merger, including shareholder redemptions and the need to secure data center capacity and GPUs.
